text.tspan: Unit labor cost by main economic activity (ISIC Rev.4), Italy
Figure illustrates the employment based unit labor costs defined as the average cost of labor per unit of output
produced. It is expressed as the ratio of total labor compensation per hour worked to output per hour worked (labor
productivity). It is measured as the annual rate of change.
Source: OECD - Productivity - Productivity and ULC by main economic activity (ISIC Rev.4)
